THE body of a 38-year-old police sergeant, attached to the Hillbrow Community Service Centre, was found on an open field in Mapleton near R103 Old Heidelberg Road on Wednesday, 6 July. A passerby herding cattle alerted authorities when he saw the body of an unknown man, who had sustained a gunshot wound to his stomach. Sergeant Siyabonga Enoch Shabalala was last seen with his sister on Tuesday on Moriri Street in Windmill Park, Joburg, when they were approached by three armed men. The suspects allegedly pushed his sister out of the vehicle, then shot and injured the off-duty officer before driving away with him. His vehicle was later recovered at Ulandolozo Street in Mailula section in Vosloorus on Wednesday. Three suspects were arrested after they were allegedly found stripping the hijacked vehicle. A firearm was also found in their possession. READ:Â Former EFF spokesman hijacked and robbed They appeared in the Boksburg Magistrates Court for charges of possession of a hijacked car and parts as well illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition. The case was postponed to Monday, 11 July. Meanwhile, five more suspects, aged between 23 and 30, were arrested by an integrated police team on Thursday, 7 July. Allegedly also involved in the killing of the sergeant, officers pounced on them in premises used as a hideout on Phelinda Street in Phumula. During a search, three firearms were recovered, including a Z88 pistol belonging to the deceased cop and 9mm beretta belonging to a security company that was robbed in Alberton in October 2021. All eight suspects were expected to appear in the Boksburg Magistrates Court on Monday to face charges of murder, kidnapping and car hijacking.